Input: nums = [-4,-2,1,4,8]
Output: 1

solution :
def closes_num(nums):
  closest=nums[0]
  for num in nums :
      if abs(num) < abs(closest): 
          closest = num 
      elif abs(num) == abs(closest) and num > closest: 
          closest = num
  return closest
nums=list(map(int,input().split()))
print(closest_num(nums))
